  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Upper and Lower Bounds Give an Absolute Bound",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(x_n)$ be a real sequence. If there exist $m,M \\in \\mathbb{R}$ such\nthat $m \\le x_n \\le M$ for every $n \\in \\mathbb{N}$, then there exists\n$K > 0$ such that $|x_n| \\le K$ for every $n \\in \\mathbb{N}$.",
